review_blob: Cherries oak and funk. Taste real tart with some hay and barnyard. So superb in the balance of the goaty funk and the cherries. Awesome.

750 ml champagne bottle.. Blue wax top. Cracked and toms of blueberry came out. Taste of blueberry wine beer and champagne combination. Definite oak in there with pretty tart mouth puckering sourness. Finished dry with the blueberries.

750 ml bottle wax top wine like simple label. Big sour cherry aroma after popping top. Taste of a combination of beer/wine/champagne with cherries all over. One of my fav brews and styles. Has tartness and cherries and other fruity esters going on. Very complex with the fruits and sour beer stuff going on. Very dry and refreshing.
beer_name: Oceanside Ale Works Up A Kriek

review_blob: Sweet syrupy guava. Seemed really thick and cloying like. Fruits smelled good. Decent carbonation. Not a fan may be I do not like this style.
Fair clarity, average aroma. Taste had bunch of vanilla in it. Threw me off. Not real bitter just ok with the off flavor of vanilla.
Big cherry aroma, thick cherry flavor. Kind of thick in cherries not as sour as most, very wine like, may be with time the funk will shoot in for the game.
A split bottle 375 I think. Cherries in aroma, not too powerful as the funky yeast came through as well, which made it great. Some oakiness more cherries and fairly dry finish.
Green apple and nice cedar stale hop aroma. Dry crisp champgne like and sour Sauvignon blanc character. Some oak in flavor and so dry and refreshing. Great style and brewery.
Love this style and brewery for sure. Green apple and sour light fruits. Light so light carbonation which made this so drinkable. Nice finish of oak and barnyard and some wet hay. Wonderful.

Awesome unreal green apple sour tart and peach aroma. No real head but some little bubble fizz. Taste tart and acidic. Some sour be easiness and sour Chardonnay light oakiness and funk. Perfect example.
Aroma ok with roast. Great black color. Nice carbonation, but real real water lean. Tang like on aftertaste. Better than most macros but way better stouts out there.
Light watery corn water. Grain lie wet grains no hops no flavor just fizzy water.
Yellow fizzy. Clear but light light yellow. No flavor just corn corn like. Drain pour or put brats in it to par boil.
Pine like fizzy some caramel and biscuit. Slightly sweet. Finishes of pine bark and some light toast.
Dark color tan head. Flavor and smell of dark malts and lean mouthfeel. Finishes roasty and crisp. Decent beer.
Very clear and carbonated. Good hops and nice light malts. Finishes with no distractions good solid go to beer.
Another great brew from TF. Big malty and even happier aroma from dark orange pour. Flavor of full malts and then big hop punch. Finishes with some alcohol but hops are the dominate trait. Excellent.
Orange clear pour. Citrus hop aroma. Flavor of fresh hops and mango and some other light fruits. Flavor is some malty and mostly hops. A must if you are a fresh hop fan.
Huge beer al around. Big roasty malty aroma. Some subdued hops. Vanilla and licorice and alcohol all big and balanced. Thick rich mouthfeel. A sipper for sure.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Copper Penney, clear and great carbonation. Hoppy aroma and nice booze notes. Very crisp for such a big brew. Biscuit malt added dimension to hops and alcohol. A sipper.
Great beer a little big for a pale but none the less a wonderful pine hop aroma and great light malty biscuit flavor with great hop taste and finish.
Sour tart nose from cloudy orange pour. Odd oak character interesting to say least kind of liked it. Finishes pretty dry and acidic.
Big malts very toffee and caramel some smoke but very little smoke more peat malt. Nice earthy happiness, great heat from alcohol but not too booze like. Finishes with mouth full of rich flavors.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Another hop bomb from port. So fresh hoppy green grassiness great pine aroma as well. Flavor of fresh grown hop plants and mellow malts. Finishes very clean. Awesome beer.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Great IPA, great big hoppy aroma, pine and eucalyptus wonderful stuff. Flavor very crisp fresh lupin glands and bitterness. Finishes very green grassy hops. Excellent.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Green apple aroma from flat pour. Taste like an old soured Chardonnay. Drinkable yes refreshing yes but just kind of one dimensional of wine like flavors.
Sour acetic acid aroma. Almost butiric some elderberries, but mostly sour. May be over time may mellow, more lambic like not bad just not balanced like the other awesome beers from here.
Golden spritz you pour. Aroma of spice wheat and coriander. Flavor is wheats and nuts, some spice and some salts but not much salt. Extremely refreshing. Great.
Perfect gose. A wonderful green apple tart aroma. Flavor of light acid and more sour light fruits. Mellow barnyard balance with a touch of minerals on a dry dry finish.m
Awesome sour and fruits in aroma. Very tart initially. Great strawberry in nose and flavor. Finishes very dry and wine like. Great brew.

Pretty damn good barley wine. Big malty aroma with some barrel age character. Taste toasty and hoppy and barrel comes through really well. Some booziness which actually was very enjoyable. A sipper for sure.
beer_name: Revolution Barrel Aged Institutionalized Barley Wine

review_blob: Very good robust porter.mroasty aroma some chocolate. Flavor of roasted malt but lean like a porter should be not to big like stout. Actually pretty refreshing if tha is good enough word for it.
Dark dark brown tan head. Vanilla smell and some fennel. Great rich palate. Flavors of cocoa and some licorice and lots of vanilla. Finishes rich.
beer_name: Revolution Barrel Aged Mad Cow Milk Stout

review_blob: Toffee aroma with citrus hops. Pretty big mouthfeel and caramel with nice hop balance. Nice lingering flavors of malts and hops.
Deep copper pour off white head. Hoppy aroma with leathery pine bark aroma and earthy mineral hop flavor with medium well balanced malts.
Amber pour light off white head. Carmel hops and some pine. Flavor is pretty malty for IPA but still pretty good.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Hazy brown pour white head 1/4 inch head. Share acidic nose with loads of raspberries. Tart flavor with a great malty balance. Caramel and red fruits in finish,

Wonderful sour, strawberries dominate nose. Sparkling cider like with peach like after tones. Light fruits through out entire flavors. Some funk and mild Brett. Very thirst quenching with really tart finish.
Amber cloudy pour really fizzy. Taste lean light malts with an added sweet caramel strangeness. All over place either too old of a brew or just not made well.
Some hops in nose, light more pale like. Hazy some yeast in suspension. Flavor of light malts and some bitterness. Good pale ale, just ok IPA.
Nice pine hop aroma, mild malts mild to heavy hop bitterness. Finished clean and piney.
Excellent, as deScription says golden and frothy. Nice white head clove and banana nose yeast lemony and so much complex flavors for a golden ale.
Damn good trip. Golden to orange fairly clear nice carb with small white head. Excellent banana with lemon zest nose and flavor of clove and banana and crisp lightly tart finish.
Brown and tan head, yeast and breads, not to much candi or dark fruits as this style has some times. Finishes pretty thick with a banana finish.
Brown pour small tan head. Not too fizzy but carb is there. Brown malts and some fruits and yeast...some spice and some tartness.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Prune and fig on a dusty brown pour with white poof head, sweet flavor with raisin and prune. Finishes a little thick not bad.
Cherry aroma is the for front. The body is light and wine like, very refreshing. Similar to a brew with Sauvignon Blanc with the added fresh cherries. Ended with sour tartness. Really nice.
Excellent. Big peach and brandy nose. Some slight oak but only adds does not distract. Flavor of peach and very light oak. The flavors of all the tart and oak and peach are so well balanced.

This breweries stuff is unbelievable! Only down side is huge money for this 750 bottle....forty bucks ouch. Never the less worth it as it has so much going on. Huge apricot aroma off the start. Poured light orange. Light head. Flavors of everything, from hay, barnyard sweet apricots and dried apricots ending of very tart acids. After all that the fresh apricots cruise back in for the finish line. A+ You gotta try this too.

This brewery rocks!!!!Only down side is huge money for this 750 bottle....forty bucks ouch. Never the less worth it as it has so much going on. Huge blackberry aroma off the start. Poured rose red. Light head. Flavors of everything, from hay, awesome fresh blackberries and ending of very tart acids. After all that the blackberries cruise back in for the finish line. A+
